I am not sure if this will completely solve the problems you are seeing, but I have spotted 2 issues that are definitely obstructing your path to a solution.

Analyzing the [Lucene.Net.Replicator.AspNetCore](https://github.com/apache/lucenenet/tree/146d7d052db27d78726697c7c777915abceede25/src/dotnet/Lucene.Net.Replicator.AspNetCore) project might also prove helpful.

### InfoStream

`InfoStream` acts like any other stream. It doesn't collect information, but it passes information along to another source. 

For performance reasons, the `ReplicationClient.InfoStream` property uses `InfoStream.NO_OUTPUT` by default. To receive `InfoStream` messages, you need to set it to another `InfoStream` implementation. For example, to write to the console output, you would need to set it an instance of `TextWriterInfoStream` that wraps `Console.Out`.

```c#
    var client = new ReplicationClient(replicator,
        new IndexReplicationHandler(handlerIndexDir, () => Notify()), new PerSessionDirectoryFactory(workingPath));

// For optimal performance in production, InfoStream should not be enabled in the release.
// Although, you may wish to add a configuration switch to your application instead of using #if DEBUG
// to make troubleshooting easier in a release build.
#if DEBUG
    // Write any InfoStream messages to the console output
    client.InfoStream = new TextWriterInfoStream(Console.Out);
#endif
```

And of course, this line will still do nothing, so it can be removed:

```c#
Console.WriteLine(client.InfoStream.ToString());
```

### Machine-Independent Paths

Linux won't recognize the paths you have setup as constants. An approach you could use to create machine-independent paths is to use the [Environment.GetFolderPath](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.environment.getfolderpath?view=netcore-3.1#System_Environment_GetFolderPath_System_Environment_SpecialFolder_) method.

```c#
var commonApplicationDataDir = Environment.GetFolderPath(Environment.SpecialFolder.CommonApplicationData);

var handlerIndexDir = Path.Combine(commonApplicationDataDir, "LuceneIndexes/handler");
var workingPathDir = Path.Combine(commonApplicationDataDir, "LuceneIndexes/clientWorkDir");
```

See [Environment.SpecialFolder Enum](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.environment.specialfolder?view=netcore-3.1) for additional options.

